                     CONTENTS OF THE EMC PHASE 4 CD

                     ---- Desktop Video Dreams ----




EMC Phase4 is a dedicated Desktop Video CD, aimed directly at Amiga users who
use their Amigas for any type of video, presentation or graphics work.

EMC Phase4 is a totally unique and professional CD Rom containing a high
proportion of copyrighted and exclusive "never seen before" material.




The EMC Phase4 CD contains...

1.  Since bitmap fonts are faster to load, access and use in most video
    applications (Scala themselves supply bitmaps!) we are including a large
    number of bitmap fonts, with IFF previews in 20 sizes between 18 point
    and 168 point.

2.  Fountain/Intellifont ready Compugraphic scalable fonts with IFF previews
    and automatic install scripts. No more messing about trying to install
    fonts, just click on an icon and the Compugraphic fonts will be installed
    into your system  ready for use!

3.  Music modules. We have used ScalaMM for years to produce corporate
    presentations for companies like the YMCA and Powersport International.
    As a direct result of this, and to satisfy our own needs, we spent many
     hours finding the best modules out of the hundreds of bad ones. For the
    first time, you will have access to music modules that you can be
    confident in using in your presentations.

4.  Sound samples. phase 4 contains hundreds of high quality sound samples
    that have been fully sorted into categories and are ideal for use as
    "spot effects".

5.  Well over 300 megabytes of "never seen before" professionally designed
    backgrounds covering subjects such as Weddings and Technology. These
    absolutely stunning backgrounds will add the professional touch to any
    video presentation and will be supplied in 800x600 24bit jpeg along with
    IFF 256 colour conversions in PAL 768x576 and NTSC 768x480 formats.

6.  Textured backgrounds, such as Marbles, Stones and Fabrics, again in full
    video overscan, that will also be supplied in 800x600 24bit jpeg,
    PAL 768x576 and NTSC 768x480 256 colour IFF formats.

7.  A selection of useful Image backgrounds, again in full video overscan,
    that can be used for a wide variety of presentation work. Again all
    supplied in 800x600 24bit jpeg, PAL 768x576 and NTSC 768x480 256 colour
    IFF formats.

8.  Program Demos. A custom created 38mb demo of the new Imagevision from
    ImageLab Technologies, a 20mb Demo of Optonica's Multimedia Experience
    and a DeluxePaint 5 demo from Electronic Arts. 

9.  Countdown timer animations, testcards, multimedia buttons, on screen
    timers, over 20 video utilities and a whole host of other stuff!




@ENDNODE

