                  EMC's INDEX CD... What is it?



The scenario...

You've got loads of clipart and Image CDs that are probably badly organised! 



The problem...

You have access to hundreds of megabytes of clipart and images but, the only
way of finding out what you've got on your CDs is to load each individual
image into an application before you can see it!

You may also need convert each image before you can even load it into your
application! 



The solution...

E.M.Computergraphic's INDEX CD. This CD contains IFF thumnail index screens
(just like EMC's Phase 1, 2 & 3 CDs) of the graphic data contained on over 30
of the most popular (not necessarily the best) CDs currently available.



CDs covered...

Pro (hahaha) Fonts & Clipart, Graphic & Adult Sensations, World of Clipart,
ProPics, Pandora, RHS Color Kollection, Aminet 3-7, Multimedia Toolkit1,
Clipart Heaven, Fresh Arte, Mother of all Clipart, PCX Potpourri, Publique
Art, SoMuchScreenware, SciFi & Fantasy, Gifs Galore, Clipart Goliath,
Clipart Warehouse, GifGalaxy and Almathera's CDPD3, Demo, Demo2, 10 on10 &
DTV CDs.



Usage...

If you are looking for a particular graphic, just load INDEX into your CD
drive and quickly scan through the thumbnail index screens via either WB or
a directory utility. Once you have located the graphic you require, remove
INDEX, and load the relevant CD into you CD drive (provided of course that
you actually have the CD the graphic is on!)... What could be simpler?

This CD offers you organisation and rapid access to the graphic data on your
CDs.

Even if you don't have all of these CDs, you can use EMC's INDEX to "see" the
contents of a  particular CD before you part with your money and buy it!



